"There are a lot of bacteria, saliva, and food debris in an oral cavity, all that can form a soft tissue, which are attached to the teeth, forming a film around them - This is the plaque. "
Az alapos fogtisztítás segíti elkerülni a fogkőképződést!

The recent scientific studies have shown that the optimal duration of tooth brushing should be 2 - 2.5 minutes. If cleaning takes less than 2 minutes, it decreases the likelihood of an effective plaque removal.
Állítsa be a fomosás időtartamát az alkalmazásban
The zones of the oral cavity
We divide the mouth into 6 zones for the hygiene and cleanliness monitoring.
In addition, the toothbrush has a built-in sensor, which will help you to determine and the next time pay more attention to those areas that have not been properly cleaned.

During tooth brushing, it is recommended to keep your head straight, so that a toothbrush could collect more accurate data. Are you worried whether the brush gathered the right information? Do not worry! The brush has a warning function: every 30 seconds it will tell you if there are more places in this areas requiring cleaning.
Develop a habit of brushing your teeth in the morning and evening
A lepedék igyekszik visszanyerni a tisztítás után 1-6 órán belül, ezért mindennap meg kell mosni a fogat legalább kétszer.
Hogyan lehet a lepedéket hastékonyan eltávolítani?
Sweet tooth is particularly exposed to the risk of plaque as well as the remnants of sugary foods increase the rate of bacterial growth
Plaque arises as a consequence of the careless or rare teeth brushing
Bacteria from the plaque can react chemically with the remains of food and form the acid substances that destroy the enamel and thus cause caries
Dental plaque due to saliva gradually gets hard and turns into dental tartar,
which causes the pathological changes in the gums and leads to the periodontitis
Bristles are one of the most important components of the toothbrush
There are thousands of bacteria in our mouth
Every day it diligently helps you to get rid of tens of thousands of different bacteria and food debris
The highest turnover rate - 37 200 times / min,A variety of massage modes,Recognition of the cleaning gestures
Typically, the bristles get deformed after 3 months of use
The bristles are erased, in consequence of which the brush head can easily injure the gums, it can also increase the number of bacteria
It is recommended to visit the dentist once every three months
